<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00032</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING LAW ENFORCEMENT PERSONNEL TO WEAR A BODY CAMERA DURING LAW ENFORCEMENT AND SPECIAL POLICE OPERATIONS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : 
Mandating Law Enforcement Personnel To Wear A Body Camera During Law Enforcement And Special Police Operations</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT :   Seeks to require law enforcement personnel to wear a body camera whenever they conduct law enforcement and special police operations intends to achieve the delicate balancing act of respecting and protecting  human rights while at the same time  protect  our law enforcement officers from harm, death or adverse legal action as they undertake their official functions. </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME :  “Body Camera Act”      </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BIAZON, ROZZANO RUFINO B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Revilla (000 2019-07-25)</td><td>2. Tambunting (000 2019-08-05)</td><tr><td>3. Lacson-Noel (000 2019-08-08)</td><td>4. Vergara (000 2019-08-14)</td><tr><td>5. Nieto (000 2019-08-20)</td><td>6. Pacquiao (R.) (000 2019-08-20)</td><tr><td>7. Barba (000 2019-08-27)</td><td>8. Rivera (000 2020-01-27)</td><tr><td>9. Villanueva (E.) (000 2020-01-27)</td><td>10. Castelo (000 2020-02-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ORDER AND SAFETY ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>